tellraw @p [{"bold":true,"color":"gold","text":"How to play:\n(You need OP)\n"},{"click_event":{"action":"run_command","command":"/tellraw @p {\"color\":\"yellow\",\"text\":\"\\nRounds:\\n\\n The number of rounds represents the number of games you play before a winner is declared. After each round, players earn points, and the player with the most points at the end of the final round is the winner. You can choose whether only the winner gets points or if all players in the top three receive points.\"}"},"color":"yellow","text":"\n[Rounds]"},{"click_event":{"action":"run_command","command":"/tellraw @p {\"color\":\"light_purple\",\"text\":\"\\nPoint of the game:\\n\\n Be the last one standing! Use your brain, PvP skills, and power-ups to eliminate or throw other players into the void. But be careful — they’ll be trying to do the same to you!\"}"},"color":"light_purple","text":"\n[Point of the game]"},{"click_event":{"action":"run_command","command":"/tellraw @p {\"color\":\"aqua\",\"text\":\"\\nGameplay:\\n\\n Everyone spawns in a random spot on the map with 3 power-ups and no friends. Your job? Eliminate the others by any means necessary — preferably before they do it to you. Oh, and natural healing is turned off, so it's better not to fall off a cliff “to get down faster”.\\n\\n Each map has two power-up spawners, marked by bedrock crosses . New power-ups spawn there every 1 minute and 15 seconds — until overtime hits. If more than one player is still alive after 5 minutes, overtime begins. The map then slowly deletes itself from the bottom up, layer by layer. This continues until there's only one survivor.\\n\\n With different maps and chaotic modifiers, no game is ever the same — except they all end in glorious destruction.\"}"},"color":"aqua","text":"\n[Gameplay]"},{"click_event":{"action":"run_command","command":"/tellraw @p {\"color\":\"green\",\"text\":\"\\n Power-ups:\\n\\n Power-ups are items that let you activate all sorts of abilities. To use one, just right-click while holding it. Each power-up has its own cooldown, depending on how  strong it is. The more powerful the ability, the longer you’ll be waiting to use it again. Patience kids.\\n\\n Collecting two of the same power-up will evolve it into a better, stronger and more annoying version.\\n\\n Want to know what a power-up does? Just read its description — or, if you’re feeling brave, use it blind and hope for the best. There are 26 power-ups in total, plus their evolved counterparts. I’d list them all, but... too much work. Discovery is half the fun anyway.\"}"},"color":"green","text":"\n[Power-ups]"},{"click_event":{"action":"run_command","command":"tellraw @p [{\"color\":\"gray\",\"text\":\"\\nMore\\n\\n Try not to leave the map while the game is on going since it might break it.\\n\\n Although this map is free, I still spent time and effort making it. If you’d like to support my work, I’ll leave a donation link below. Every donation is greatly appreciated!\"},{\"bold\":true,\"click_event\":{\"action\":\"open_url\",\"url\":\"https://buymeacoffee.com/hazardislands\"},\"text\":\"\\n\\n[Donate here]\"}]"},"color":"gray","text":"\n[More]"}]